adoc: R. H. Wood \n* 1904 Cardigan: [[John William Willis-Bund]]\n* 1905 Shrewsbury: [[David Thomas (Archdeacon of Montgomery)|D. H. Thomas]], [[Archdeacon of Montgomery]] \n* 1906 Carmarthen: [[Sir John Williams, 1st Baronet, of the City of London|Sir John Williams 1st Baronet]] \n* 1907 Llangefni: Sir Richard H. Williams Bulkely\n* 1908 Monmouth: [[Archibald Sayce|Rev Prof A. H. Sayce]]\n[[File:Henry Hoyle Howorth, Vanity Fair, 1895-07-11.jpg|thumb|[[Henry Hoyle Howorth|Sir Henry Hoyle Howarth]], president 1908\u201309, ''[[Vanity Fair (UK magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'', 1895]] \n* 1909 Chester: [[Henry Hoyle Howorth|Sir Henry Hoyle Howarth]]\n* 1910 Llandrindod Wells: [[Charles Dillwyn-Venables-Llewellyn]] \n* 1911 Abergele: [[William Boyd Dawkins|Professor William Boyd Dawkins]] \n* 1912 Cardiff: [[Robert Windsor-Clive, 1st Earl of Plymouth]] \n* 1913 Devizes: [[William Boyd Dawkins|Professor William Boyd Dawkins]]\n* 1914 Shrewsbury: [[William Boyd Dawkins|Professor William Boyd Dawkins]]\n* 1915 Shrewsbury: [[William Boyd Dawkins|Professor William Boyd Dawkins]]\n* 1916 Shrewsbury:[[William Boyd Dawkins|Professor William Boyd Dawkins]]\n* 1917 Shrewsbury: [[William Boyd Dawkins|Professor William Boyd Dawkins]]\n* 1918 Shrewsbury: [[William Boyd Dawkins|Professor William Boyd Dawkins]]\n* 1919 Dolgellau: Sir E. Vincent Evans \n* 1920 Swansea: Lt Col W. Ll. Morgan \n* 1921 Ruthin: [[Sir E Vincent Evans]]\n* 1922 Haverfordwest: [[Sir Evan Davies Jones, 1st Baronet|Sir Evan D. Jones Bt]] MP\n* 1923 Oswestry: Prof [[J. E. Lloyd]] \n* 1924 Brittany: [[Herbert John Fleure|Prof H. G. Fleure]]\n* 1925 Llandeilo Fawr: Hon. Charles Urien Rhys MP\n* 1926 Pwllheli: [[Willoughby Gardner]] \n* 1927 Hereford: [[Rev E. Hermitage Day]] \n* 1928 Aberafan: H. J. Randall\n* 1929 Douglas, Isle of Man: [[P. M. C. Kermode]]\n* 1930 Menai Bridge: [[Harold Hughes (architect)|H Harold Hughes]]\n* 1931 Lampeter: [[Mortimer Wheeler]]\n* 1932 Newtown: [[R. A. Stewart Macalister|Prof R. A. S. Macalister]]\n* 1933 Cardiff: [[Cyril Fox]]\n* 1934 Galway: [[R. A. Stewart Macalister|Prof R. A. S. Macalister]]\n* 1935 Llangollen: [[Archdeacon C. F. Roberts]]\n* 1936 Abergavenny: [[W. D. Car\u00f6e]] \n* 1937 Bangor: [[Sir John Edward Lloyd]] \n* 1938 Tenby: [[David Prosser (bishop)|Rev D. L. Prosser, Bishop of St David's]] \n* 1939 Shrewsbury Emergency Meeting \n* 1940\u20131945 No Meeting \n* 1946 Aberystwyth: [[David Ormsby-Gore, 5th Baron Harlech]]\n* 1947 Rhyl: [[Baron Mostyn|Lord Mostyn]] \n* 1948 Carmarthen: [[David Prosser (bishop)|Rev D. L. Prosser, Archbishop of Wales]] \n* 1949 Harlech: [[Ifor Williams|Sir Ifor Williams]]\n* 1950 Carlisle: Sir Ifor Williams\n* 1951 Brecon: [[Edward Williamson]], Bishop of Swansea and Brecon \n* 1952 Bangor: [[Robert Richards (Welsh politician)|Robert Richards]] MP\n* 1953 Chepstow: [[Victor Erle Nash-Williams|V. E. Nash Williams]]\n* 1954 Shrewsbury: [[John Davies Knatchbull Lloyd|J. D. K. Lloyd]]\n* 1955 Nefyn: [[Wilfrid James Hemp]] \n* 1956 Haverfordwest: Sir Frederick Rees, [[High Sheriff of Pembrokeshire]] \n* 1957 Bala: [[Ellis Davies (priest)|Canon Ellis Davies]]\n* 1958 Presteigne: [[Thomas Alwyn Lloyd|T. Alwyn Lloyd]]\n* 1959 Ruthin: Professor [[A. H. Dodd]] \n* 1960 Swansea: Professor William Rees\n* 1961 Dublin: [[Ralegh Radford|C. A. Ralegh Radford]]    \n* 1962 Newtown: E. D. Jones    \n* 1963 Cardiff: Professor [[W. F. Grimes]]\n* 1964 Llangefni: Professor [[T. Jones Pierce]]\n* 1965 Hereford: Bishop [[Glyn Simon]] of Llandaff\n* 1966 Chester: George Lloyd\n[[File:Emrys George Bowen.jpg|thumb|Prof [[E. G. Bowen]], president 1966\u201367]]\n* 1967 Carmarthen: Professor [[E. G. Bowen]]\n* 1968 Glasgow: Professor [[Idris Foster]]\n* 1969 Vale of Conway: [[A. J. Taylor]] \n* 1970 Caerleon: E. I. P. Bowen \n* 1971 Harlech: C. E. Vaughan Owen \n* 1972 Lampeter: [[A. H. A. Hogg]]\n* 1973 Wrexham: [[H. Mostyn Lewis]] \n* 1974 South Brecknock: Canon J. Jones Davies\n* 1975 Winchester: [[Dr H. N. Savoury]]\n* 1976 